The [main page for Setting up SSL for Confluence|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Running+Confluence+Over+SSL+or+HTTPS] does have a disclaimer as quoted below.

There is [another page|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Connecting+to+LDAP+or+JIRA+or+Other+Services+via+SSL] for setting up Confluence with different services over SSL (Connecting+to+LDAP+or+JIRA+or+Other+Services+via+SSL), which does not carry same message that can be misleading to customers coming directly into the later resource, creating a false expectation for support on the matter.

Would it be possible to add it to https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Connecting+to+LDAP+or+JIRA+or+Other+Services+via+SSL ?

{quote}
This page documents configuration of SSL, rather than of Confluence itself. Atlassian will support Confluence with this configuration, but we cannot guarantee to help you debug problems with SSL. Please be aware that this material is provided for your information only, and that you use it at your own risk.
{quote}

