The 'Widget Connector' only appears to work with a very specific URL from Google Maps. Due to a recent update in Google's side, it doesn't seem to be possible to generate links like this one anymore:

{noformat}
https://maps.google.com/maps?q=Atlassian,+George+Street,+New+South+Wales,+Australia&hl=en&ll=-33.866572,151.207001&spn=0.004321,0.008256&sll=-33.870509,151.203707&sspn=0.008641,0.016512&oq=atlassian,&hq=Atlassian,+George+Street,+New+South+Wales,+Australia&radius=15000&t=m&z=18&iwloc=A
{noformat}

Even when accessing the link above directly, the URL gets automatically converted to:

{noformat}
https://www.google.com/maps/place/Atlassian/@-33.866572,151.207001,18z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x6b12ae408eafffbf:0xe6e6afa8ffbe707?hl=en
{noformat}

This last URL doesn't seem to be automatically converted using the 'Widget Connector', thus failing to display/render the map inside a Confluence page.

*Workaround*

Tried multiple ways to workaround the situation and get the old URL from Google, but we're constantly getting directed to the new URL format. At the moment, we *don't* have a workaround to this scenario.

