All pages on confluence.atlassian.com take over 20 seconds to load in a browser. Based on my testing, the culprit appears to be a malformed {{<script>}} tag that looks something like this:

{code}
<script src="//http://cdn.optimizely.com/js/1053703113.js"></script>
{code}

By starting the URL with {{//}}, it becomes a protocol-relative URL -- as a result, the browser tries to load {{https://http://cdn.optimizely.com/js/1053703113.js}}, which takes a very long time to resolve and ultimately returns no content. Because the script tag is not loaded asynchronously, the browser blocks and the page doesn't render until this URL returns.

The solution is simple -- just remove {{http://}} from the URL. The script tag should look like this:

{code}
<script src="//cdn.optimizely.com/js/1053703113.js"></script>
{code}

